# 07.05 cmdOS Desktop Agent

## Overview

The cmdOS Desktop Agent defines the desktop execution experience where AI Agents can understand user intent and perform actions directly within the user's computer environment.

Unlike traditional desktop applications, cmdOS Desktop Agent acts as an intelligent execution layer between humans and operating systems.

The user does not need to manually operate every application.

Instead:

User Intent

↓

Desktop Agent

↓

Application Understanding

↓

Action Execution

↓

Result

---

# 1. Desktop Agent Purpose

The purpose of cmdOS Desktop Agent is to enable AI-powered interaction with desktop environments.

It allows users to:

- Control applications
- Manage files
- Automate workflows
- Execute tasks
- Connect multiple applications

